  <div xmlns:v="http://rdf.data-vocabulary.org/#" typeof="v:Review">
    <div class="main review-item" id="1418998">
        

  <header class="main-hd">
    <h3 class="title">
      <a href="https://book.douban.com/review/1418998/" class="title-link">失忆的味蕊</a>
      <div class="toggle_review right">        <a href="javascript:;" id="toggle-1418998"class="indicator unfold j" title="展开全文">        </a>
      </div>
    </h3>
    

<div class="header-more">
    <a class="author-avatar" href="https://www.douban.com/people/lemon4bb/"><img width="48" height="48" src="https://img3.doubanio.com/icon/u1231700-1.jpg"></a>
    <a href="https://www.douban.com/people/lemon4bb/" class="author">
      <span property="v:reviewer">清心·薄荷</span>
    </a>    <span property="v:rating" class="allstar50 main-title-rating" title="力荐"></span>
  <span property="v:dtreviewed" content="2008-06-24"
      class="main-meta">2008-06-24 15:52:19</span>
</div>

  </header>

        <div class="main-bd">
          <div id="review_1418998_short" class="review-short">
            <div class="short-content">
                  看《香港味道》时我对作者和他搜罗的一众好友的味觉记忆颇为妒忌，怎么他有那么多关于食物的故事可讲，怎么几十年过去，他们或她们对某种味道的丝缕依然清晰如昨故而死忠追崇。我以为自己在这方面的回味是匮乏的，似乎想不起来从小到大品尝过堪称人间美食的惊奇。  错觉罢了。...

                  <div class="more-info pl clearfix">
                    <span class="left">1有用 / 0没用</span>
